After the crates have been packed with 200 pipes each, what is the positive difference in the total heights (in cm) of the two packings?

solution:
In Crate A, we have 20 rows of 10 pipes packed directly on top of each other.  So the height of the packing is 20 times the diameter of a single pipe, or 200 cm. In Crate B, draw a horizontal line through the centers of the 9 or 10 pipes in each row. By symmetry, the distance between each consecutive pair of these 21 lines will be the same, say equal to $d$.  There will be 20 such distances.

